#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Basic test script for IsHash validator"""

import hashlib
from dirty_equals import IsHash

def test_ishash():
    """Test IsHash validator functionality"""
    
    # Test MD5
    md5_hash = 'd41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e'
    assert md5_hash == IsHash('md5')
    assert md5_hash.upper() == IsHash('md5')
    
    # Test SHA256
    sha256_hash = hashlib.sha256(b'test').hexdigest()
    assert sha256_hash == IsHash('sha256')
    
    # Test invalid cases
    assert 'invalid' != IsHash('md5')
    assert 'abc' != IsHash('sha256')
    
    # Test repr case preservation
    assert repr(IsHash('MD5')) == "IsHash('MD5')"
    assert repr(IsHash('sha256')) == "IsHash('sha256')"
    
    # Test unsupported algorithm
    try:
        IsHash('unsupported')
        assert False, "Should have raised ValueError"
    except ValueError as e:
        assert 'Unsupported hash algorithm' in str(e)
    
    print("✅ All IsHash tests passed! [YOYOYO]")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    test_ishash()
